added.title: The Drip
added.description: Robin finally experiences drip, a magical coolness that comes from wearing sneakers, and soon seeks out the ultimate pair.

added.title: Lil' Dimples
added.description: Thinking it's a way to reconnect with her father, Raven enters a beauty pageant.

added.title: The Hive Five
added.description: Tired of the Titans, The Hive agrees to take a day off and avoid engaging with their foes - if possible.

added.title: You're Fired
added.description: Beast Boy gets fired from the team and the Wonder Twins take his place.

added.title: Real Magic
added.description: Robin dabbles with magic, ignoring Raven's warning that he will anger the magic god.

added.title: The Authority
added.description: Granny JoJo's overprotective behavior puts the Wattersons in danger...from themselves.

added.title: The Storm
added.description: Love is in the air and Gumball is caught in the center of an emotional hurricane - literally!

added.title: Hashtag #1 Fan
added.description: Panda gets kidnapped by a pair of deranged French foxes.

added.title: Snow Place Like Home
added.description: When the Bears realize whatever they build with snow comes to life they decide to build the biggest snow party of all time.

added.title: Kelsey the Worthy
added.description: When Kelsey demolishes a wall at Craig's house, her father takes away her sword. So she enlists Craig and JP to help prove to her father that she's still worthy.

added.title: The End Was Here
added.description: Craig tries to figure out how an ancient war that decimated the Creek began in hopes of stopping history from repeating itself.

added.title: In the Key of the Creek
added.description: When a rainy day keeps Craig inside, he uses his toys and imagination to create his own Creek adventure in Craig of the Creek's first musical episode!

added.title: Van Hogling
added.description: Chef and the kids take a field trip to Sugar's farm but  ignore all of Sugar's strict and boring farm rules has dire consequences when Chef and the kids unleash a herd of ravenous "Were-hogs" on a full moon.

added.title: Ticking Crime Bomb
added.description: Leshawna and Izzy trick Owen into thinking he's destined to be a criminal mastermind, but when he leaves school to join the scariest gang in town, they have to mount a rescue attempt.

added.title: Weiner Takes All
added.description: After forgetting to book a Hot Diggity Doggity Dog mascot on National Hotdog Day, Chef tries to pass off an Australian man dressed as a kangaroo as a substitute.

added.title: Apoca-lice Now
added.description: When Chef brokers a truce with lice by selecting three kids to "host" them on their heads, Courtney instigates a kid vs. lice war.

added.title: Gnome More Mister Nice Guy
added.description: When the daycare gets taken over by evil gnomes, Duncan finds himself on the wrong team.

added.title: Dragonhead
added.description: In desperate need of a shower due, Apple and Onion resort to desperate measures.

added.title: Pulling Your Weight
added.description: Apple and Onion join a gym to gain the strength of seven people.

added.title: Rotten Apple
added.description: Onion's Dad becomes convinced that Apple is a bad influence on his son.

added.title: The Inbetween
added.description: Apple and Onion have promised they will be there for Falafel's birthday party. However, they find themselves in a mysterious place and don't know how to get out.

added.title: Election Day
added.description: Apple and Onion realize that the Mayor of their city is corrupt and they vow to put an end to that.

added.title: Mr. Flabby Daddy Wabby Jabby
added.description: The Jellystone kids disguise themselves as an adult to get into a movie, but soon have to live a life they didn't expect.

added.title: Ice Ice Daddy
added.description: Captain Caveman discovers he has a long-lost son and tries to make up for centuries of lost time.

added.title: Moor Fogg
added.description: Team Tennyson goes international in the Omni-Copter and the first stop is for a hike in the Scottish Highlands, but the weather isn't just bad, it's foggy, and that means one thing and one thing only: the return of The Fogg!

added.title: Speechless on the Seine
added.description: While in Paris, France, Ben catches Zombozo robbing the Louvre, but when Zombozo hypnotizes Ben to remain speechless, Ben must navigate a foreign land like a mime in order to stop the criminal clown and his travelling circus.

added.title: Big in Japan
added.description: During a tour of the Japanese Robotics Museum, Ben finds hero-gone-wrong Tim Buktu "trying to save" Tokyo from a Dragon. Has Tim finally turned over a new leaf, or is this just another one of his half-baked plans to play the part of hero?

added.title: Big Ben 10
added.description: When Ben and family go to London to visit the legendary Big Ben, the Bugg Brothers are there to greet them, with yet another outrageously over the top plan of course: to shrink the Big Ben bell in order to steal it!

added.title: Lickety Split
added.description: When a mysterious electrical storm downs the Omni-Copter at the Equator, Team Tennyson soon discovers Solar & Polar are behind it, but when Ben accidentally combines the two into a more powerful Uni-Twin, our hero must think fast if he is going to save the planet!

added.title: Temporal Tedium
added.description: It's Fizzness Time! What does that even mean? Elliott and Mo make it their thing to find out as they meet Preston, a slow, yet hilarious prankster with a penchant for jewelry.

added.title: Companion Confusion
added.description: After a failed experiment in trying to find true love, Mo has to save Elliott from being sucked off the Centrium into outer space.

added.title: #TheAquamanCometh
added.description: For months, Garth's been sending Aquaman letters that greatly exaggerate his accomplishments in Metropolis, so when the King of Atlantis comes for a surprise visit, Garth begs the Super Hero Girls to help cover for his little white lies.

added.title: #OneEnchantedEvening
added.description: Zee worries that Zatara is lonely and volunteers to play matchmaker for her dad.  But when her meddlesome match-matching accidentally sets her dad up with an old enemy, Zee must find a way to fix the mess she made!

added.title: #NightmareInGotham
added.description: Babs and Harleen bring the Girls to Gotham City to celebrate Halloween! However, the fun is put on hold when the SuperHero Girls run into Gotham's most notorious SuperVillain.

added.title: Go Fish
added.description: While on a fishing trip, the Bears get attacked by a giant legendary fish.

added.title: Googs
added.description: The Bears win a tour of the infamous Googs corporate headquarters.

added.title: Paperboyz
added.description: The Baby Bears get jobs as paper boys.

added.title: Bear Squad
added.description: Tabes deputizes the Bears so they can go to the city and catch a thief.

added.title: Best Bears
added.description: The Bears must complete their Best-Man duties on the day of Darrell's wedding.

added.title: Storm in the Room
added.description: Steven goes into his room in the temple to look for answers.

added.title: Rocknaldo
added.description: Ronaldo sets out to find all the rock people living in Beach City!

added.title: Tiger Philanthropist
added.description: Steven returns to the ring to continue his pro wrestling odyssey.

added.title: Alone at Sea
added.description: Steven and Greg take a boat trip out to sea and find themselves in dangerous water.

added.title: Greg the Babysitter
added.description: Steven learns the tale of how Greg came to work at the car wash.

added.title: Mumm-Ra, the Ever-Living
added.description: Every time Mumm-Ra gets a hold of a magic artifact to restore his powers, the ThunderCats just smash it and turn him into a dinky skeleton again. Until today that is, because Mumm-Ra just remembered he's got the Ancient Spirits of Evil, and now he can get swole whenever he wants!

added.title: Berserkers
added.description: The Cats' Lair is attacked by gold-loving robot pirates, the Berserkers! This is a good thing, really, since it means Lion-O and the ThunderKittens can ditch their chores and fight robo-pirates instead! Just don't tell Tygra!!!!

added.title: Jaga History
added.description: Freed from the Astral Plane, Jaga, ghost of the ThunderCats mentor, is now free to visit the Cats' Lair. Which means he can finally tell them why Thundera, their home world, exploded. It's story time!

added.title: Barbastella
added.description: While flying with his new invention, Panthro hits it off with a new friend, Barbastella, the Queen of the Bats! Now Panthro needs help getting ready for his big date with her, because it turns out Panthro is terrified of bats! Lion-O and Cheetara are happy to help but, wow, that is a lot to unpack.

added.title: Adopt a Jackal
added.description: After a battle with the Mutants, Jackalman gets confused and accidentally returns to the Cats' Lair with the Thundercats, he is the dumbest mutant. Jackalman pretends to be a Thundercat so his enemies won't catch him and the Thundercats pretend to play along because they feel bad for him!

added.title: The Speedway Five-Billion
added.description: Unagami's soldiers, the Red Visors, finally discover the secret location of Scott's garage and attack the ninja, who manage to escape with the help of Racer Seven, and enter the spectacular Speedway Five Billion.

added.title: Stop, Drop and Side Scroll
added.description: Our ninja barely have time to mourn the loss of their fallen ninja friends before being thrust into the madness of Terra Domina where Lloyd will have to face an old adversary from his past.

added.title: Ninjago Confidential
added.description: Back in Ninjago City, Zane and Pixal hit the mean streets to track down Milton Dyer, only to discover that things are not what they seem.

added.title: The Prodigal Father
added.description: Zane, kidnapped by the Mechanic, faces Unagami. Master Wu fights to free Zane, while Pixal questions Milton Dyer for information on how to shut down Prime Empire.

added.title: The Temple of Madness
added.description: Jay must stand alone against Unagami in the end-game, yet Unagami has a bigger battle in facing the truth about his own identity.

added.title: Lucky Ducky Mug
added.description: When Adorabat and Badgerclops break Mao Mao's favorite mug, he gives them the silent treatment.

added.title: Lonely Kid
added.description: When AD has trouble making friends at school, MM tells her the story of how he made his first real friend —BB.

added.title: Try Hard
added.description: When the Sky Pirates take Mao Mao and Badgerclops hostage, it's up to Adorabat to save the day.

added.title: Scared of Puppets
added.description: Mao Mao is scared of puppets.

added.title: The Perfect Couple
added.description: When Mao Mao accidentally breaks up the most perfect couple in Pure Heart Valley, he has to figure out how to get them back together.

added.title: Bear-Knuckle Brawl
added.description: Axel must team up with Bearbarian to stop Madcap from transforming Luka's stuffed bear collection into an invincible army.

added.title: Saving Private Masko
added.description: Masko takes Axel's call for more discipline too seriously and loses sight of his own identity in the process, becoming a no-nonsense soldier set on toeing the line - and ill-equipped for a lucha libre with Madcap!

added.title: On Your Toes
added.description: After a Porcupunk sighting, Axel leads a recon mission that slowly but surely proves to be a wild goose chase devised by Sarge, who's secretly pursuing a hobby that he's afraid to share with his teammates.

added.title: Friend Wars
added.description: Princess SugarSalt dupes Axel into hanging out with Cleo LeBall and usurps his role as team leader, forcing Zoe to step in and keep the toys together.

added.title: The Bakugan Battle League Dash/The Final Stage
added.description: The Bakugan Battle League Dash: With Dan and Ajit eliminated from the Bakugan Battle League - Tokyo Edition, the remaining Awesome Brawlers - Shun, Wynton, Lia and Lightning race to complete the second stage of the competition. In order to make it to the final stage, the gang will have to pull together to defeat some tough competition./The Final Stage: It's the final stage of the Bakugan Battle League Tokyo Edition! The remaining Awesome Brawlers are ready to go, but just as the final round begins, the competitors are surprised with some unwelcome guests.

added.title: The Tokyo Catastrophe/Bakugan Battle League Finale
added.description: The Tokyo Catastrophe: Haavik has highjacked the Bakugan Battle league - Tokyo Edition! He's been using the tournament as a platform for his sinister plot to bring chaos and destruction to the city of Tokyo./Bakugan Battle League Finale: Haavik unleashes an army of unruly Bakugan to bring his own brand of chaos and destruction to the city of Tokyo. It's all hands-on-deck to stop the invasion, and foil Haavik's plot.

added.title: Champion of the Universe, Dan!/Operation Babysitter
added.description: Champion of the Universe, Dan!: Dan starts "sleep brawling", rolling out Drago causing damage and confusion while he's fast asleep. With the help of a "sleep expert", Ajit attempts to stop Dan and put his "sleep brawling" to rest once and for all./Operation Babysitter: Ajit lands a job babysitting a rambunctious toddler - Aiden. Having no experience with kids, Ajit recruits Wynton to help him out. Things get a little out of hand when Aiden rolls out - Krakelious. Now, Ajit and Wynton have a tiny Baku-brawler on their hands, with no way to stop him!

added.title: Beastie Team Battle/Ajit and Lia
added.description: Beastie Team Battle: China Riot is on the lookout for a partner to team up with in the new Bakugan battle team tournament being held in Los Volmos. Riot may have only been after a brawling partner, but ends up with a new friend./Ajit and Lia: Lia knows the story of where Ajit found his Golden Baku-balls, but no one knows "how" he's able to partner with Golden Bakugan. To get the inside scoop, Lia tags along with Ajit at his new job as a security guard at the local Museum.

added.title: Once More into the Maze/Grandpas in the Wild
added.description: Once More into the Maze: Storm, McQ, Sophie and Everett were spotted at the ruins where the great core cell is housed! Alarmed by the report from Benton Dusk, the Awesome Brawlers head to the Yucatan Peninsula to investigate./Grandpas in the Wild: During an all-out brawl with Storm, McQ, Sophie and Everett, the Awesome Brawlers are hit with an attack that sends everyone spiraling to various parts of the maze. Split up from the rest of the gang, Wynton and Lightning find themselves in a strange unfamiliar part of the maze. While trying to get their bearings, they discover some new golden allies.

added.title: P.L.O.T. Device 2: Beyond the Bored Dome
added.description: Dr. Fox reprograms the P.L.O.T. Device to only generate boring events, but the gang can't help but add drama and excitement to every scenario.

added.title: The New Nemesis
added.description: When Hawkodile discovers his old enemy Eagleator has a new nemesis in his life, the gang do all they can to get Hawk back on his foe's radar.

added.title: Baby Caterpillar
added.description: Unikitty takes in a radioactive caterpillar and raises it like a baby, unaware of the havoc it will wreak as a full-grown adult.

added.title: Borrowed
added.description: Richard discovers his library books have been borrowed by Master Frown and sets off on a crazed mission to return the books before they're overdue.

added.title: Best Best Friends
added.description: Master Frown and Brock attend a friendship-themed competition intending to ruin it for everyone else, but soon discover their own friendship in need of repair.

added.title: Deep Space Vacation
added.description: When Gar lets KO and Enid take a vacation to outer  space, they get more than they bargained for.

added.title: Big Reveal
added.description: KO finds out who his father is.

added.title: Radical Rescue
added.description: Rad is forced to reconsider his identity when KO starts taking on some of his traits.

added.title: You're a Good Friend, KO
added.description: KO brings Dendy along for a hero mission in order to cheer her up.

added.title: Let's Get Shadowy
added.description: KO teams up with an unlikely ally to take on an old foe.

added.title: The Headsucker's Moxy/Equal Fights
added.description: The Headsucker's Moxy: There's a mysterious villain in town who's sucking pertinent information from the brains of powerful people and committing crimes. How do the girls trap this sucker before his next victim is drained?/Equal Fights: When the girls try to catch a local female villain, she tells them that as women they've got to stick together. It's up to the women of Townsville to teach our heroines the true meaning of equality.

added.title: A Made Up Story
added.description: Someone is defacing all the posters and statues of Townsville with make-up. Can the girls stop this makeover takeover or will they get the blush off?

added.title: Beat Your Greens/Down N' Dirty
added.description: Beat Your Greens: When Broccoli Aliens from space invade Townsville, it's up to the Powerpuff Girls and all the children of Townsville to take a bite out of crime. Down N' Dirty: When Buttercup refuses to take a bath, the town kicks her out. But Buttercup decides to stick with her stink until her favorite thing is taken away from her.

added.title: Custody Battle/City of Nutsville
added.description: Custody Battle: Mojo discovers the Rowdyruff Boys are back and is determined to show them that he is a more evil dad than Him./The City of Nutsville: The squirrels of Townsville are chirping mad! But when Bubbles loses her ability to speak a squirrel, the girls don't know how to calm the rodents down.

added.title: Jewel of the Aisle/Super Zeroes
added.description: Jewel of the Isle: A crook hides a huge diamond in a box of the girls' favorite cereal. But how can he trick the girls into giving him some cereal in order to get the jewel back?/Super Zeroes: The girls don't think they have enough superhero accessories like those found in the comic books. They begin to emulate their favorite characters, complete with gadgets and gizmos.

added.title: Imaginary Fiend/Cootie Gras
added.description: Imaginary Fiend: The new boy in school has a special friend nobody else can see. When this imaginary friend begins destroying the class, the girls must imagine how to stop him./Cootie Gras: Mojo observes that everyone is staying away from little Harry Pitt because he has cooties. So Mojo concocts a plan to keep the girls away by using this cootie-covered boy as bait.

added.title: Twisted Sister/Cover Up
added.description: Twisted Sister: The girls decide they need some help fighting crime so they create another Powerpuff Girl. But they don't get the combination of sugar, spice and everything nice quite right./Cover Up: Blossom and Bubbles learn that Buttercup has secretly been rubbing a security blanket before every battle to make herself a super fighter. Can the girls convince Buttercup that her strength is within?

added.title: Candy Is Dandy/Catastrophe
added.description: Candy Is Dandy: When the Mayor gives the girls some candy in gratitude for saving the day, they become hooked on the stuff. They even make a deal with a local villain to commit crimes for treats./Catastrophe: A monster is frantically tearing up the town looking for his lost kitty. But in a city the size of Townsville, how can the girls find one lone cat?

added.title: Crazy Mixed Up Puffs/Mizzen in Action
added.description: Crazy Mixed Up Puffs: The girls must literally work as one to try and stop Mojo from destroying Townsville./Mizzen in Action: Captain Crack McGraigen and his crew are tossed forward in time where discover the chemical X that marks the spot and it is up to the girls and Professor to send the super-charged pirates back to their own time.

added.title: Rebel Rebel
added.description: The Professor makes new friends, but they may be the wrong crowd.

added.title: Our Brand is Chaos
added.description: Bubbles and Buttercup make a deal without realizing the consequences.

added.title: Tagalong
added.description: Buttercup is tired of Bubbles following her everywhere.

added.title: Brainlord
added.description: A new superhero arrives in Townsville with a dark secret.

added.title: Checkin' Out!
added.description: A trip to the supermarket has bizarre consequences.

added.title: Under Wraps
added.description: When Ben and Gwen are sent to a farm to learn the value of hard work, what they really learn is that an evil alien mummy has arrived on Earth.

added.title: The Return
added.description: Ghostfreak has returned! And he has brought a Mummy, Werewolf and Frankenstein like aliens with him to help him shroud the Earth in darkness.

added.title: The Visitor
added.description: A mysterious alien named Xylene shows up and wants to return the Omnitrix to its rightful owner, Grandpa Max!

added.title: Something Zombozo This Way Comes
added.description: Ben and Rook must stop Zombozo and the Circus Freaks from turning everyone in Bellwood into zombie clowns!

added.title: Bengeance is Mine
added.description: Vilgax' former lackey Psyphon is elated when his master returns.

added.title: Animo Crackers
added.description: Dr. Animo from the future comes back to the present to help himself defeat Ben once and for all. (Introducing new Ben alien, Gutrot.)

added.title: Charmed, I'm Sure
added.description: Still stranded on the monster planet Anur Transyl, Ben and Rook reluctantly team up with Charmcaster to take on Zs' Skayr.

added.title: Catfight
added.description: The princesses Looma and Attea are at odds over who gets to marry Ben!

added.title: The Lesson
added.description: Gumball and Darwin get put in detention and quickly find it's more like prison than school. And there's only one thing to do in prison... ESCAPE!

added.title: The Photo
added.description: It's school picture day and Gumball has until 3pm to take one good photo - or have his legacy ruined forever.

added.title: The Tape
added.description: Gumball and Darwin fail to make some instant homemade movie classics.

added.title: Hoyuelitos
added.description: Raven compite en un certamen de belleza, creyendo que es la forma de reconectarse con su padre.

added.title: Pizza Hero
added.description: It's the end of the school year, and as is tradition at Aberdale Elementary, Papa Marianio is slated to dish out his famous pizza along with a spectacle of song and dance. As the kids wait in excitement, they share memories about times with Papa.

added.title: Sumo Goes West
added.description: Clarence learns his best friend Sumo may transfer to another school! It's up to Clarence to protest, petition and rally to convince everyone to let Sumo stay - or face losing his closest school pal!

added.title: Valentimes
added.description: When Clarence notices his teacher Ms. Baker is the only one in class left without a Valentine this year, he decides to enlist the help of Sumo to set her up with Sumo's teacher, Mr. Mozer! Will sparks fly or will the boy's naive view of romance backfire?

added.title: Rock Show
added.description: Chad's band Dogmon, plays a show for the first time in years, giving Clarence and Mary a chance to really rock out.

added.title: The Boxcurse Children
added.description: Clarence, Jeff, and Sumo stumble upon a mysterious box. After they open it, some strange things begin to happen. Convinced they've unlocked a curse, they become determined to reverse it!

added.title: Trucker Hall of Fame
added.description: Mordecai and Rigby have to help Muscle Man get to the Big Rig Museum to spread his dad's hat's ashes.

added.title: Out of Commission
added.description: Mordecai and Rigby have one last day with the cart before they have to get rid of it.

added.title: Fancy Restaurant
added.description: Muscle Man has to impress his girlfriend's parents at a fancy dinner.

added.title: Diary
added.description: Mordecai and Rigby want to fix a lock on Margaret's diary before she gets back from a weekend trip.

added.title: The Best VHS in the World
added.description: Mordecai and Rigby have to return an overdue VHS to the store so they won't be banned from renting new movies.

added.title: De Pesca
added.description: Durante un viaje de pesca, los osos son atacados por un enorme pez legendario.

added.title: Googs
added.description: Los osos ganan un tour a las oficinas de una importante empresa.

added.title: Osos Repartidores
added.description: Los ositos comienzan a trabajar de repartidores de periódicos.

added.title: Escuadron Osuno
added.description: Tabes permite que los osos tomen su lugar para que vayan a la ciudad y atrapen a un ladrón.

added.title: Osos Padrinos
added.description: Los osos deben cumplir sus tareas de padrinos en la boda de Darrell.

added.title: Grande en Japón
added.description: Durante un recorrido por el Museo de Robótica Japonés, Ben encuentra a Tim Buktu, un héroe que fue por el mal camino, "tratando de salvar" a Tokio de un Dragón. ¿Tim cambió por fin o este no es más que otro de sus planes mal concebido para hacer el papel de héroe?

added.title: La Neblina del Paramo
added.description: El equipo Tennyson se hace internacional en el Omni-Copter, y la primera parada incluye una caminata por las Tierras Altas de Escocia. Pero el clima no es sólo malo, sino que hay niebla, y eso puede significa solamente una cosa: iel regreso de Niebla!

added.title: Insomnio en el Sena
added.description: Durante su estadía en París, Francia, Ben descubre a Zombozo en pleno robo en el Louvre. Pero cuando Zombozo hipnotiza a Ben para que se quede sin palabras, Ben debe navegar por una tierra extranjera como un mimo para detener al payaso criminal y su circo ambulante.

added.title: Separacion Rapida
added.description: Cuando una misteriosa tormenta eléctrica se abate sobre el Omni-Copter en el Ecuador, el equipo Tennyson pronto descubre que Solar y Polar están detrás del suceso.

added.title: Big Ben 10
added.description: Cuando Ben y su familia viajan a Londres para visitar el legendario Big Ben, los hermanos Bicho están allí para darles la bienvenida, obviamente con un nuevo plan escandalosamente exagerado: iencoger la campana del Big Ben para robarla!

added.title: It Came From the Nightosphere
added.description: Against Marceline's wishes, Finn conjures her father, the Lord of Evil, and attempts to reconcile their rocky relationship. But when the Lord of Evil discovers his daughter has turned the family axe into a bass guitar, he takes it from her and starts sucking up all the souls in Ooo! Finn must find a way to stop the Lord of Evil and get Marceline's guitar back.

added.title: Loyalty to the King
added.description: There's a new "Nice King" in Ooo, and he looks kinda like someone else we know.

added.title: Slow Love
added.description: A lonely snail lookin' for love literally crashes into the treehouse and asks Finn and Jake for help. Now, our heroes must teach this snail how to get a girlfriend before he destroys their home!

added.title: Power Animal
added.description: Finn is kidnapped by a group of gnomes, who want to harness his energy to take over the world. Only Jake can save his best friend if he can just focus long enough to follow the obvious clues and rescue Finn.

added.title: Carrera Cinco Billones por Hora
added.description: Los soldados de Unagami, los Visores Rojos, finalmente descubren la ubicación secreta del garaje de Scott y atacan a los Ninjas.

added.title: Her Parents
added.description: Jake pretends to be a rainicorn in order to make Lady's parents like him.

added.title: Detenerse, Caer y Girar
added.description: Los Ninjas no han ni llorado la pérdida de sus amigos  caídos cuando ya deben entrar a la locura de Tierra Domina.

added.title: Ninjago Confidencial
added.description: De vuelta en la ciudad de Ninjago, Zane y Pixal salen a las calles para encontrar a Milton Dyer, y descubren que las cosas no son lo que parecen…

added.title: El Padre Prodigo
added.description: Zane, secuestrado por el Mecánico mientras Pixal interroga a Milton Dyer para obtener información sobre cómo cerrar el Primer Imperio.

added.title: El Templo de la Locura
added.description: Jay debe enfrentarse solo a Unagami en el juego final, pero Unagami tiene una batalla más grande al enfrentarse a la verdad sobre su propia identidad.

added.title: Kelsey la merecedora
added.description: Cuando Kelsey demuele una pared de la casa de Craig, su padre le quita la espada. Por eso, Kelsey les pide ayuda a Craig y a JP para que le demuestren a su padre que aún la merece.
added.originalseriesname: Craig of the Creek en Espanol

added.title: Llego el final
added.description: Craig intenta comprender cómo se desató una antigua antigua que diezmó la población del Arroyo, con la esperanza de evitar que la historia se repita.
added.originalseriesname: Craig of the Creek en Espanol

added.title: Nickname
added.description: When a kid wants a cool nickname, UG tells him he has to earn it in the most legendary way ever: yard work!

added.title: Driver's Test
added.description: When a girl has trouble passing her driving test, Uncle Grandpa shows up to help her.  But when they accidentally set a Crazy Baby loose in the city, it's up to Uncle Grandpa to stop it... by teaching the girl how to drive!

added.title: Uncle Grandpa Sitter
added.description: Gus and Pizza Steve have plans to go out for the night, but UG can't be left alone in the RV, so they need a babysitter.  But when none are available, they turn to UG to babysit himself.

added.title: Uncle Grandpa Ate My Homework
added.description: When Uncle Grandpa shows up and mistakenly eats a kid's Egyptian diorama for school, he helps the kid bring an actual pyramid to class, but accidentally unleashes an evil mummy on the world.

added.title: Uncle Grandpa for a Day
added.description: When UG gets his head stuck in a peanut butter jar, Mr. Gus and Pizza Steve have to pretend to be UG and help a kid.

added.title: Pelea de Nudillos de Oso
added.description: Axel debe formar equipo con Bearbarian para evitar que Madcap transforme la colección de osos de peluche de Luka en un ejército invencible.

added.title: Salvar al Soldado Masko
